sentences: Ana Karylle Padilla Tatlonghari (born March 22, 1981), known mononymously as Karylle, is a Filipino singer-songwriter, actress, dancer, TV host, model, athlete, musical theater performer, and entrepreneur.
In 2002, she won "Best New Artist" at the MTV Philippines.
Karylle was born on March 22, 1981, in Manila to Zsa Zsa Padilla, a singer-actress and Dr. Modesto Tatlonghari.
Her second album was released on 2005 entitled You Make Me Sing.
Her fourth album, Roadtrip, was released in 2011; she produced the album by herself.
Karylle's fifth album, which is simply entitled K, was launched in November 2013.
The album also includes Karylle's 2013 Philpop entry Sa’yo
In 2015, Universal Records released Karylle Songbook containing her first two albums in one CD.
Her latest and sixth album, entitled A Different Playground, was launched in February 2016.
Karylle's first appearance on a movie was for a cameo role in Imus Productions' Metro Manila Filmfest entry in 2002 Ang Agimat as Maria Makiling.

After her successful stint in the Saturday series, Karylle took on a challenging role as Denise Alferos in the 2010 International Emmy nominee for Telenovela category, Dahil May Isang Ikaw.
